1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a framework for resource allocation in a communication system, which is a core topic in networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of future channel gains for optimizing resource allocation, which is a topic closely related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a policy for joint optimization of resource allocation for real-time and non-real-time services, which is a topic related to systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper considers video-on-demand (VoD) services as an example, which is a topic related to multimedia. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses resource allocation in a communication system, which is a topic related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing.
